description._content: Original Collection: Presidents of Oregon State University Photographic Collection (P 1) Item Number: P1:69 Image Description: Frank L. Ballard graduated with a B.S. in agriculture in 1916. He served as the Vice Director of the Extension Service until he was appointed the President of Oregon State College. After a short term as President, Ballard returned to the Extension Service, eventually becoming the Extension Service Head from 1945-1961.
